Entities = ["Mar de la Vida OJSC", 979893388, "Oceanfront Oasis Inc Carriers", 8327]
viewof EntitiesI = Inputs.select(Entities, {label: "Choose an entity"})
import {directedGraph} from "c21fd57894972d18"
dg2 = {
const nodes = [
mc1.nodes.find(d => d.id === EntitiesI),
...mc1.nodes.filter(n =>
mc1.links.filter(d => d.target ===EntitiesI).some(s => s.source === n.id) ||
mc1.links.filter(d => d.source === EntitiesI).some(t => t.target === n.id)
)
]
const links = [
...mc1.links.filter(d => d.target === EntitiesI),
...mc1.links.filter(d => d.source === EntitiesI)
]
return {nodes, links}
}
directedGraph({data: dg2, height: 900, nodeSpacing: 200})
mutable node_option = "All";
mutable link_option = "All";
function createNodeTypeDropdown() {
const nodeTypes = Array.from(new Set(mc1.nodes.map(node => node.type)));
nodeTypes.unshift("All");

const dropdown = document.createElement("select");

dropdown.addEventListener("change", function() {
mutable node_option = dropdown.value;
});

nodeTypes.forEach(function(nodeType) {
const option = document.createElement("option");
option.text = nodeType;
dropdown.appendChild(option);
});

return dropdown;
}
function createLinkTypeDropdown() {
const linkTypes = Array.from(new Set(mc1.links.map(node => node.type)));
linkTypes.unshift("All");


const dropdown = document.createElement("select");

dropdown.addEventListener("change", function() {
mutable link_option = dropdown.value;
});

linkTypes.forEach(function(linkType) {
const option = document.createElement("option");
option.text = linkType;
dropdown.appendChild(option);
});

return dropdown;
}
nodeTypeDropdown = createNodeTypeDropdown();
linkTypeDropdown = createLinkTypeDropdown();
mutable nodeAttributes = {};
dg3 = {
const width = 1800;
const height = 1000;

// Map each node 'type' to a unique number
const typeToNumber = new Map(Array.from(new Set(mc1.nodes.map(node => node.type))).map((type, i) => [type, i]));

const color = d3.scaleOrdinal(d3.schemeBuGn);
const specialColor = "red";
const highlightColor = "yellow"; // Color to highlight the selected node type

const links = mc1.links.map(d => ({...d}));
const nodes = mc1.nodes.map(d => ({...d}));

const simulation = d3.forceSimulation(nodes)
.force("link", d3.forceLink(links).id(d => d.id))
.force("charge", d3.forceManyBody())
.force("center", d3.forceCenter(width / 2, height / 2))
.on("tick", ticked);

const svg = d3.create("svg")
.attr("width", width)
.attr("height", height)
.attr("viewBox", [0, 0, width, height])
.attr("style", "max-width: 100%; height: auto;");


const link = svg.append("g")
// .attr("stroke", getLinkColor) // use a function to determine the stroke color
.attr("stroke", d => {
if (!d) {
console.log('Undefined link:', d);
return '#000';
}
if (d.type === linkTypeDropdown.value) {
return "#999";
} else {
return "transparent";
}
})

.attr("stroke-opacity", 0.6)
.selectAll("line")
.data(links)
.join("line")
.attr("stroke-width", d => Math.sqrt(d.value));

const node = svg.append("g")
.attr("stroke", "#fff")
.attr("stroke-width", 1.5)
.selectAll("circle")
.data(nodes)
.join("circle")
.attr("r", 5)
.attr("fill", getNodeColor);

node.on("click", function(d) {
mutable nodeAttributes = JSON.stringify(d, null, 2);
});

node.append("title")
.text(d => d.id);

// Add a drag behavior.
node.call(d3.drag()
.on("start", dragstarted)
.on("drag", dragged)
.on("end", dragended));

function getNodeColor(d) {
if (Entities.includes(d.id)) {
return specialColor;
} else if (d.type === nodeTypeDropdown.value) {
return highlightColor;
} else {
return color(typeToNumber.get(d.type));
}
}

function getLinkColor(d) {
if (d.type === linkTypeDropdown.value) {
return "green"; // Change this to the color you want for the selected link type
} else {
return "#999"; // Default color
}
}
// Set the position attributes of links and nodes each time the simulation ticks.
function ticked() {
link
.attr("x1", d => d.source.x)
.attr("y1", d => d.source.y)
.attr("x2", d => d.target.x)
.attr("y2", d => d.target.y)
.attr("stroke", getLinkColor); // Update stroke color based on the selected link type


node
.attr("cx", d => d.x)
.attr("cy", d => d.y);
}

// Reheat the simulation when drag starts, and fix the subject position.
function dragstarted(event) {
if (!event.active) simulation.alphaTarget(0.3).restart();
event.subject.fx = event.subject.x;
event.subject.fy = event.subject.y;
}

// Update the subject (dragged node) position during drag.
function dragged(event) {
event.subject.fx = event.x;
event.subject.fy = event.y;
}

// Restore the target alpha so the simulation cools after dragging ends.
// Unfix the subject position now that it‚Äôs no longer being dragged.
function dragended(event) {
if (!event.active) simulation.alphaTarget(0);
event.subject.fx = null;
event.subject.fy = null;
}

// When this cell is re-run, stop the previous simulation.
invalidation.then(() => simulation.stop());

return svg.node();
}

d3_6 = require("d3@6")
drag_simu = simulation => {
function dragstarted(event) {
if (!event.active) simulation.alphaTarget(0.3).restart();
event.subject.fx = event.subject.x;
event.subject.fy = event.subject.y;
}
function dragged(event) {
event.subject.fx = event.x;
event.subject.fy = event.y;
}
function dragended(event) {
if (!event.active) simulation.alphaTarget(0);
event.subject.fx = null;
event.subject.fy = null;
}
return d3_6.drag()
.on("start", dragstarted)
.on("drag", dragged)
.on("end", dragended);
}
gradient_markers = {
const sg = "#FFA500";
const dg = "#00FF00";
const ig = "#FF00FF";
return d => {
switch(d.degree) {
case 'suspect':
return sg;
case 'direct':
return dg;
case 'indirect':
return ig;
default:
return ["gray"];
}
};
}
function filterData(mc1, Entities, directLinkCount, indirectLinkCount) {
const directLinks = mc1.links.filter(link => Entities.includes(link.source) || Entities.includes(link.target));

let directNodeIDs = [...new Set(directLinks.flatMap(link => [link.source, link.target]))];

const indirectLinks = mc1.links.filter(link => directNodeIDs.includes(link.source) || directNodeIDs.includes(link.target));
let indirectNodeIDs = [...new Set(indirectLinks.flatMap(link => [link.source, link.target]))];

const nodes = mc1.nodes.filter(node => indirectNodeIDs.includes(node.id)).map(node => {
if (Entities.includes(node.id)) {
return {...node, degree: 'suspect'};
} else if (directNodeIDs.includes(node.id)) {
return {...node, degree: 'direct'};
} else {
return {...node, degree: 'indirect'};
}
});

// Adjust the number of direct and indirect links based on the provided counts
const filteredDirectLinks = directLinks.slice(0, directLinkCount);
const filteredIndirectLinks = indirectLinks.slice(0, indirectLinkCount);
const links = [...filteredDirectLinks, ...filteredIndirectLinks];

return {nodes, links};
}

viewof directLinks = Inputs.text({label: "Direct Links"})
viewof inDirectLinks = Inputs.text({label: "InDirect Links"})
filtered_data = filterData(mc1, Entities, directLinks, inDirectLinks);
colors = {
const entityColor = "red";
const directColor = "blue";
const indirectColor = "green";
return d => {
switch(d.degree) {
case 'suspect':
return entityColor;
case 'direct':
return directColor;
case 'indirect':
return indirectColor;
default:
return "gray";
}
};
}
createForceDirectedGraph = {
const graphLinks = filtered_data.links.map(link => ({ ...link }));
const graphNodes = filtered_data.nodes.map(node => ({ ...node }));

const simulation = d3_6
.forceSimulation(graphNodes)
.force("link", d3_6.forceLink(graphLinks).id(node => node.id))
.force("charge", d3_6.forceManyBody())
.force("center", d3_6.forceCenter(width / 2, 2000 / 2));

const svg = d3_6.create("svg").attr("viewBox", [0, 0, width, 2000]);

const linkGroup = svg.append("g")
.attr("stroke", "#999")
.attr("stroke-opacity", 0.6);

const links = linkGroup.selectAll("line")
.data(graphLinks)
.join("line")
.attr("stroke-width", link => Math.sqrt(link.value));

const nodeGroup = svg.append("g")
.attr("stroke", "#fff")
.attr("stroke-width", 1.5);

const nodes = nodeGroup.selectAll("circle")
.data(graphNodes)
.join("circle")
.attr("r", 5)
.attr("fill", colors)
.call(drag_simu(simulation))
.on("mouseenter", (event, node) => {
links
.attr("display", "none")
.filter(link => link.source.id === node.id || link.target.id === node.id)
.attr("display", "block");
})
.on("mouseleave", () => {
links.attr("display", "block");
});

nodes.append("title").text(node => node.id);

simulation.on("tick", () => {
links
.attr("x1", link => link.source.x)
.attr("y1", link => link.source.y)
.attr("x2", link => link.target.x)
.attr("y2", link => link.target.y);

nodes.attr("cx", node => node.x).attr("cy", node => node.y);
});

invalidation.then(() => simulation.stop());

return svg.node();
}
There are a few patterns that may indicate illegal activity. First, all of the entities are somewhat ambiguous. They are either not clearly defined or they are not registered to any known entity. This suggests that the people involved in the illegal activity are trying to conceal their identities. Second, the entities are all linked to Russia. This is significant because Russia is a known hotbed of cybercrime. Third, the entities are all related to phone numbers. This suggests that the illegal activity may involve phone scams or other forms of fraud.

However, it is important to note that there is no concrete evidence that any of these entities are involved in illegal activity. The patterns I have identified are just suggestive, and they could be explained by other factors. For example, the ambiguity of the entities could simply be due to a lack of information. And the links to Russia could be innocent, such as if the people involved in the illegal activity are simply Russian nationals.

Overall, I am confident that there are patterns that may indicate illegal activity
